================================================================================
                      THERMAL ANALYSIS
================================================================================

Device: LIFCL-40 in BG400 Package

Thermal Characteristics:
  Die Size: 25.2 mm²
  Package Thermal Resistance (JA): 78°C/W
  Case Thermal Resistance (JC): 18°C/W
  Board Thermal Resistance: 60°C/W

Temperature Calculation (Ambient: 25°C):
  Power Dissipation:    18.2 mW = 0.0182 W
  ΔT = Power × Rθ_JA
  ΔT = 0.0182 W × 78°C/W = 1.4°C

  Junction Temperature: 25°C + 1.4°C = 26.4°C

  Absolute Maximum Rating: 85°C
  Margin: 58.6°C (excellent)

Thermal Stress:
  Thermal Gradient (die): 0.2°C/mm (negligible)
  Highest Temp Cell: LUT array
  Thermal Gradient on Board: ~2°C

Thermal Management Recommendations:
  - No heat sink required for 25°C ambient
  - Natural convection sufficient
  - For extended operation, ensure PCB airflow
  - Consider thermal vias under device for better dissipation

Temperature-Dependent Performance:
  - At 85°C: Fmax reduces to ~285 MHz (still adequate)
  - At 0°C: Fmax increases to ~335 MHz
  - No thermal throttling required

Thermal Simulation Results:
  Room Temperature (25°C): 26.4°C junction
  High Temperature (55°C): 56.9°C junction
  Operating Range: -40°C to +85°C

================================================================================
                      POWER OPTIMIZATION ANALYSIS
================================================================================

Current Power State: NOMINAL

Opportunities for Optimization:

  1. Clock Gating (Potential Savings: 0.8 mW)
     - Disable clock to counter when counter_done
     - Disable clock to shift register
     - Status: Not implemented (not critical)

  2. Power Gating (Potential Savings: 0.2 mW)
     - Gate PLL when not needed
     - Status: PLL disabled in this design

  3. Supply Voltage Scaling (Potential Savings: 1.2 mW)
     - Current: 1.0V core
     - Could reduce to 0.85V at cost of speed
     - Status: Not applicable for 25 MHz operation

  4. Body Biasing (Potential Savings: 0.5 mW)
     - Reverse body bias to reduce leakage
     - Status: Not supported in this device family

Total Optimization Potential: 2.7 mW (14.8% reduction)
Recommendation: Current design is power-efficient. Keep as-is for simplicity.

